&lt;h2 id="rendering-mathematical-equations"&gt;Rendering mathematical equations
 &lt;a href="#rendering-mathematical-equations"&gt;&lt;svg class="anchor-symbol" aria-hidden="true" height="26" width="26" viewBox="0 0 22 22" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
 &lt;path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="currentColor"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
 &lt;path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
 &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Examples from the 
&lt;a href="https://www.mathjax.org/#demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;mathjax demo&lt;/a&gt;.
But they work with &lt;code&gt;katex&lt;/code&gt; as well.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h3 id="rmarkdown"&gt;Rmarkdown
 &lt;a href="#rmarkdown"&gt;&lt;svg class="anchor-symbol" aria-hidden="true" height="26" width="26" viewBox="0 0 22 22" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
 &lt;path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="currentColor"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
 &lt;path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
 &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In &lt;code&gt;.Rmarkdown&lt;/code&gt; documents, you can use either&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;$a \ne 0$
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;to get inline math: &lt;code&gt;\(a \ne 0\)&lt;/code&gt;.
There is no conflict with using dollar symbols regularly, because &lt;code&gt;knitr&lt;/code&gt; automatically escapes freestanding dollar symbols.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And you can use&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;$x = {-b \pm \sqrt{b^2-4ac} \over 2a}.$$
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;to get a math paragraph:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$$x = {-b \pm \sqrt{b^2-4ac} \over 2a}.$$&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h3 id="md"&gt;md
 &lt;a href="#md"&gt;&lt;svg class="anchor-symbol" aria-hidden="true" height="26" width="26" viewBox="0 0 22 22" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"&gt;
 &lt;path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="currentColor"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
 &lt;path d="M3.9 12c0-1.71 1.39-3.1 3.1-3.1h4V7H7c-2.76.0-5 2.24-5 5s2.24 5 5 5h4v-1.9H7c-1.71.0-3.1-1.39-3.1-3.1zM8 13h8v-2H8v2zm9-6h-4v1.9h4c1.71.0 3.1 1.39 3.1 3.1s-1.39 3.1-3.1 3.1h-4V17h4c2.76.0 5-2.24 5-5s-2.24-5-5-5z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;
 &lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In &lt;code&gt;.md&lt;/code&gt; documents, you can &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; use the single dollar syntax.
The double dollar syntax still gives you a math paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;$$x = {-b \pm \sqrt{b^2-4ac} \over 2a}.$$
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;$$x = {-b \pm \sqrt{b^2-4ac} \over 2a}$$&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to get inline equations, use:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0"&gt;&lt;code&gt;`\(a \ne 0\)`
or
\\(a \ne 0\\)
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;to get: &lt;code&gt;\(a \ne 0\)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>